  "name": "RPlog_Corellia-Bound",
  "title": "Corellia-Bound",
  "summary": "Aboard the New Republic cruiser Rapier, the Mon Calamari Senator Tokoga and Commander Rasi Cen brief the newly arrived Ambassador Ambrosia Delgard on their mission to unite Corellia's scattered, leaderless revolutionary cells against the Empire. They recount how Imperial brutality against striking CEC shipyard workers spawned militant groups that now need the Republic's trust and coordination, and Ambrosia draws on her diplomatic experience to advise listening to the people's grievances. Interrupted by a comm call from her young daughter Gabi, Ambrosia briefly steps out, betraying the maternal caution that has tempered her once guns-blazing style. The party agrees to depart within hours aboard a Kale-1 scout disguised in plain dress, with a YT-1300 of marines dropping in first to secure the meeting. They gather in the hangar, Ambrosia having shed her finery and wedding ring for the disguise, ready to fly to Corellia and make contact with the freedom fighters.",
